author: Christina Zhao
title: Arizona Joins Virginia, Maryland and D.C. in Enacting Stay-at-Home Order Amid Escalation in COVID-19 Cases
description: The "Stay Home, Stay Healthy, Stay Connected" executive order will go into effect at 5 p.m. local time on Tuesday.
content:
Arizona Governor Doug Ducey on Monday joined several other U.S. state leaders in enacting a stay-at-home order amid the coronavirus pandemic.
